  "description": [
    "Roosevelt Appeals for Ratification of Child Labor Change Letters to 19 Governors Ask Amendment Be Made One of Major Items on Programs Bv United Frees President Roosevelt today appealed to the governors and governorselect of 19 states to make ratification of the Child Labor Amendment to the Constitution a major item on their 1937 legislative programs Roosevelt sounded his appeal in letters which directed attention to the fact that approval by 12 more states would make effective the amendment which empowers Con gress to limit regulate and prohibit the labor of persons under 18 Twen tyfour dates already have ratified the change The Chief Executive pointed out that nationwide minimum stand ard are necessary and that a way thould be found promptly to crystal lize in legal safeguards public opin ion in behalf of the elimination of child labor FOLLOWS MESSAGE Roosevelts letter followed closely his reference to child labor in his annual message to Congress Wednes day Then he said that under NRA provisions positive gains were made but pointed out that it was unwise to expect the same agency to rule on social questions and complicated economic ones as well The Presidents letter said It is clearly Indicated"
  ],
